-- C11 GAP WITNESS. Direct `target ∈ xs` on a Seq is silently DROPPED
-- by the oracle (it cannot translate Seq membership to a Z3 Bool;
-- `target` does not even appear in the emitted SMT2). Here target=99
-- is NOT in xs, yet the constraint vanishes and the claim is vacuously
-- SAT → exit 0. If Seq membership ever compiles, this fixture FLIPS to
-- exit 2 and this expectation must be revisited. This documents the gap.
-- entry: main
-- expect: exit = 0
import "stdlib/kernel.ev"
claim main
    xs ∈ Seq(Int) = ⟨1, 2, 3⟩
    target ∈ Int = 99
    target ∈ xs
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = ⟨Exit(0)⟩
